---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { getCollection } from 'astro:content';

const allPosts = await getCollection('posts', ({ data }) => {
  return data.draft !== true && data.category === 'The Sender and The Sent';
});

const posts = allPosts.sort((a, b) => b.data.date.valueOf() - a.data.date.valueOf());
---

<BaseLayout
  title="The Sender & The Sent — Nazaryah"
  description="Scripture presents two distinct roles — never three. Father and Son, Husband and Bride, Kinsman Redeemer and the price paid. From Genesis to Revelation, one sends, one is sent."
>
  <div class="tr-wrap">

    <!-- ── HERO ── -->
    <section class="tr-hero">
      <a href="/trinity" class="tr-back">&#8592; Back to Trinity</a>
      <p class="tr-label">&#8213; Two Roles, One Covenant Plan &#8213;</p>
      <h1 class="tr-title">The Sender &amp; The Sent</h1>
      <p class="tr-sub">
        Scripture never presents three. It presents two — one who sends, and one who is sent. From the first pages of Torah to the last pages of Revelation, this pattern does not break.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- ── INTRO ── -->
    <section class="tr-section">
      <div class="tr-prose">
        <p>
          The Trinity doctrine collapses a clear covenant structure into a philosophical abstraction. But the text is not abstract. It is relational, directional, and deeply consistent. The Father gives a command — the Son carries it out. The Father sends — the Son goes. The Father glorifies — the Son receives the glory.
        </p>
        <p>
          These studies examine those roles directly: what the titles actually mean, where they come from in Hebrew Scripture, and what happens when they are placed back into their original covenant context rather than read through the lens of Nicaea.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── POST LIST ── -->
    <section class="tr-posts-section">
      <div class="tr-posts-grid">
        {posts.map((post) => (
          <a href={`/blog/${post.slug}`} class="tr-post-card">
            <div class="tr-post-meta">
              <span class="tr-post-date">
                {post.data.date.toLocaleDateString('en-US', { year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric' })}
              </span>
            </div>
            <h2 class="tr-post-title">{post.data.title}</h2>
            <p class="tr-post-desc">{post.data.description}</p>
            <span class="tr-post-read">Read Study &nbsp;&#8594;</span>
          </a>
        ))}
      </div>

      {posts.length === 0 && (
        <div class="tr-empty">
          <p>Studies are being prepared. Check back soon.</p>
        </div>
      )}
    </section>

    <!-- ── QUOTE ── -->
    <section class="tr-footer-quote">
      <p class="tr-quote-text">"For I have come down from heaven, not to do my own will, but the will of him who sent me."</p>
      <p class="tr-quote-ref">— John 6:38</p>
    </section>

  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .tr-wrap {
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, #0e0904 0%, #1a1208 20%, #160f07 100%);
    color: #f0e0bf;
    font-family: 'Crimson Pro', 'Crimson Text', Georgia, serif;
    min-height: 80vh;
  }

  .tr-hero {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 4rem 1.5rem 3rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #4a3218;
    background:
      radial-gradient(ellipse at 50% 0%, rgba(150, 90, 40, 0.18), transparent 70%),
      linear-gradient(180deg, #0a0602 0%, #1a1208 100%);
    position: relative;
  }

  .tr-back {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    color: #8a6028;
    text-decoration: none;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }
  .tr-back:hover { color: #c4a46b; }

  .tr-label {
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 4px;
    color: #8a6028;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .tr-title {
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.2rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #f0e0bf;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    line-height: 1.1;
  }

  .tr-sub {
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 2vw, 1.15rem);
    color: #c4a46b;
    font-style: italic;
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .tr-section {
    padding: 3rem 1.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #2e1f0d;
  }

  .tr-prose {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: #dcc99a;
  }
  .tr-prose p { margin-bottom: 1.2rem; }

  .tr-posts-section {
    padding: 3.5rem 1.5rem;
    max-width: 860px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .tr-posts-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .tr-post-card {
    display: block;
    background: rgba(30, 18, 8, 0.7);
    border: 1px solid #3a2410;
    border-radius: 4px;
    padding: 1.8rem 2rem;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: border-color 0.2s, background 0.2s;
  }
  .tr-post-card:hover {
    border-color: #8a6028;
    background: rgba(50, 30, 10, 0.7);
  }

  .tr-post-meta {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .tr-post-date {
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    color: #7a5520;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .tr-post-title {
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: clamp(1.1rem, 2.5vw, 1.4rem);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #f0e0bf;
    margin: 0 0 0.6rem;
    line-height: 1.3;
  }

  .tr-post-desc {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: #b09060;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }

  .tr-post-read {
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    color: #8a6028;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .tr-empty {
    text-align: center;
    color: #7a5520;
    font-style: italic;
    padding: 3rem 0;
  }

  .tr-footer-quote {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 3rem 1.5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid #2e1f0d;
  }

  .tr-quote-text {
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 2vw, 1.2rem);
    color: #c4a46b;
    font-style: italic;
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: 0 auto 0.5rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .tr-quote-ref {
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    color: #7a5520;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }
</style>
